SUMMARY:Money Smart: Organizational Types
DESCRIPTION:Pros and Cons of Business Structures\nConfused about the type of business structure you should use? Explore with us the pros and cons of each type to determine which organizational type best fits your small business goals.\nWe’ll explore the unique characteristics\, benefits\, and potential drawbacks of:\n• Sole Proprietorship\n• Partnerships\n• Limited Liability Company (LLC)\n• C-Corporation\n• S-Corporation \nJoin the West Virginia District Office of the U.S. Small Business Administration (SBA) and the West Virginia Small Business Administration for the series Money Smart for Small Business. This series provides a practical introduction to starting and managing a business that is ideal for both aspiring and established entrepreneurs. The series was developed jointly by the Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation (FIDC) and the SBA. Each virtual session comes with a practical workbook guide. Sessions are Wednesdays at 11:30 am beginning March 18\, 2026\, through May 27\, 2026. Register for the sessions that fit your schedule and needs. These sessions will not be recorded.
URL:https://wvbusinesslink.com/event/money-smart-organizational-types/
LOCATION:Microsoft Teams
CATEGORIES:Business Training
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://wvbusinesslink.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Money-Smart-Organizational-Types.png
ORGANIZER;CN="U.S. Small Business Administration":MAILTO:wvinfo@sba.gov
END:VEVENT
