SUMMARY:Money Smart: Recordkeeping
DESCRIPTION:Learn practical recordkeeping skills and tools to make smarter decisions and streamline your small business operations.\nWe’ll cover:\n• Essential recordkeeping practices\n• How these recordkeeping methods function in everyday operations\n• Exploring software solutions designed to simplify small business recordkeeping \nJoin the West Virginia District Office of the U.S. Small Business Administration (SBA) and the West Virginia Small Business Administration for the series Money Smart for Small Business. This series provides a practical introduction to starting and managing a business that is ideal for both aspiring and established entrepreneurs. The series was developed jointly by the Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation (FIDC) and the SBA. Each virtual session comes with a practical workbook guide. Sessions are Wednesdays at 11:30 am beginning March 18\, 2026\, through May 27\, 2026. Register for the sessions that fit your schedule and needs. These sessions will not be recorded.
URL:https://wvbusinesslink.com/event/money-smart-recordkeeping/
LOCATION:Microsoft Teams
CATEGORIES:Business Training
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://wvbusinesslink.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Money-Smart-Recordkeeping-2.png
